#### Phase 5: CSRF Protection Evaluation âœ… COMPLETE

**Status**: ğŸŸ¢ **LOW RISK** - No CSRF protection needed

**Architecture Analysis**:
- âœ… JWT header-based authentication (`Authorization: Bearer <token>`)
- âœ… **Zero cookies** used in the application
- âœ… Stateless design (no session cookies)
- âœ… Custom headers not sent automatically by browsers
- âœ… Same-Origin Policy prevents cross-origin header injection

**CSRF Attack Scenario**:
```javascript
// âŒ This attack FAILS with Q-Collector
<form action="https://qcollector.com/api/v1/forms/123/delete" method="POST">
  <input type="submit">
</form>
<script>document.forms[0].submit();</script>

// Why it fails:
// 1. No Authorization header sent (browser doesn't send custom headers cross-origin)
// 2. Backend returns 401: "Authentication token required"
// 3. Attack blocked at authentication layer
```

**Cookie Audit Results**:
```bash
grep -rn "res\.cookie\|req\.cookies" backend/ --include="*.js"
# Result: Zero cookie usage found âœ…
```

**Documentation Created**:
- âœ… [CSRF-ASSESSMENT.md](./CSRF-ASSESSMENT.md) - Comprehensive risk analysis
- âœ… Explains why CSRF protection is not needed
- âœ… Lists conditions for future reassessment

**Decision**: â›” DO NOT IMPLEMENT CSRF protection (not needed for header-based auth)

